<div id="review_59171997" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/59171997" />
    <a title="Shannon" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/360248-shannon"><img alt="Shannon" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/59171997?book_show_action=true">Jun 10, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Shannon" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Shannon" href="/user/show/360248-shannon">Shannon</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer59171997" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3088369372691624888">What I find most amazing about this book is that Ayla somehow is managing to invent everything known to modern man. Fire, domesticated horses, dogs as pets, baby food, etc...you name it, and the perfect Ayla is doing it. It&apos;s too incredible to make the book seem real. And she&apos;s too perfect to make her seem like a real character. <br/><br/>Not to mention, I am bored by the pages and pages of descriptive text about every plant, animal and cave dwelling Ayla comes across. WHERE IS THE PLOT!!?!?!??!<br/><br/>I am more </span>
  <span id="freeText3088369372691624888" style="display:none">What I find most amazing about this book is that Ayla somehow is managing to invent everything known to modern man. Fire, domesticated horses, dogs as pets, baby food, etc...you name it, and the perfect Ayla is doing it. It's too incredible to make the book seem real. And she's too perfect to make her seem like a real character. <br /><br />Not to mention, I am bored by the pages and pages of descriptive text about every plant, animal and cave dwelling Ayla comes across. WHERE IS THE PLOT!!?!?!??!<br /><br />I am more than mid-way through the book and have not seen much of a plot yet...thinking about just giving up on reading this one. Except, I don't want to miss where she invents the wheel, and I assume that's coming since she has not invented it...yet.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3088369372691624888" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

